main event: Multiple witnesses reported observing unusual lights and objects in the sky over Orlando, Florida between May 6 and May 22, 1966.
interesting points: Witnesses described varying colors of lights, including blue, green, red, and white, that moved with great speed and changed shape,Several witnesses reported seeing a hovering object that changed color and moved slowly downward,Orlando Sentinel received over 40 calls from residents reporting sightings,The USAF received communications regarding the sightings, including descriptions from different witnesses, and multiple reports under Project Blue Book were filed,The nature of the sightings led to conclusions being categorized as potentially astronomical or unidentified.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects and strange glowing lights
witness description: Civilians, including a radio announcer and general public residents in Orlando.
